dification Guide (link to docs/modificationGuide.md)\n\n6. **Directories Section**\n   - Show project structure using ASCII tree format\n   - Add numbered explanations for each major directory\n   - Example:\n   ```\n   â”œâ”€â”€ Backend/\n   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ [backend-folder-name]/\n   â”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ bin/\n   â”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ lambda/\n   â”‚       â””â”€â”€ lib/\n   â”œâ”€â”€ docs/\n   â”œâ”€â”€ frontend/\n   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ src/\n   â””â”€â”€ README.md\n   ```\n   Then explain each directory's purpose\n\n7. **Credits Section**\n   - List all contributors with LinkedIn links\n   - **If LinkedIn URLs not provided**: Use format:\n     `This application was developed by [CONTRIBUTOR_NAME - INSERT_LINKEDIN_URL], [CONTRIBUTOR_NAME - INSERT_LINKEDIN_URL]`\n   - Acknowledge teams and supporters\n   - Example format:\n     ```markdown\n     This application was architected and developed by <a href=\"[INSERT_LINKEDIN_URL]\" target=\"_blank\">[Name]</a>, <a href=\"[INSERT_LINKEDIN_URL]\" target=\"_blank\">[Name]</a>, with [role] <a href=\"[INSERT_LINKEDIN_URL]\" target=\"_blank\">[Name]</a>.\n     ```\n\n8. **License Section**\n   - State the license type\n   - Link to LICENSE file\n\n---\n\n## PART 2: docs/architectureDeepDive.md\n\n### Structure Requirements:\n\n1. **Title: \"Architecture Deep Dive\"**\n\n2. **Architecture Diagram** (Same as README, placed at top)\n   - `![Architecture Diagram](./media/architecture.jpeg)`\n   - **If not provided**: Add placeholder note:\n     > **[PLACEHOLDER]** Architecture diagram needed. Please create a diagram showing the complete system architecture and save it as `docs/media/architecture.png`\n\n3. **Numbered Flow Explanation**\n   - Describe the architecture flow step-by-step\n   - Number each step (1, 2, 3...)\n   - Explain what happens at each stage\n   - Keep it simple and user-friendly\n   - Example format:\n   ```\n   1. Upload: User requests permission to upload files via /endpoint.\n   2. File Storage: User uploads documents to secure storage.\n   3. Processing: System processes the uploaded files.\n   ```\n\n4. **Cloud Services / Technology Stack Section**\n   - List each service/technology used\n   - Use bullet points with **bold service names**\n   - Under each service, provide:\n     - Brief description of its role\n     - Specific functions/components it handles (sub-bullets)\n   - Example:\n   ```markdown\n   - **API Gateway**: Acts as the front door for all requests\n   - **Lambda Functions**:\n     - **function_name_1**: Description of what it does\n     - **function_name_2**: Description of what it does\n   - **Database Service**: Stores application data\n   ```\n\n5. **Infrastructure as Code Section** (if applicable)\n   - Explain how infrastructure is defined and deployed\n   - Mention tools used (CDK, Terraform, CloudFormation, etc.)\n   - Explain deployment automation scripts\n\n---\n\n## PART 3: docs/deploymentGuide.md\n\n### Structure Requirements:\n\n1. **Title: \"Deployment Guide\"**\n\n2. **Table of Contents**\n   - Auto-generate links to all sections\n   - Use nested structure for subsections\n   - Example:\n   ```markdown\n   - [Deployment Guide](#deployment-guide)\n     - [Requirements](#requirements)\n     - [Pre-Deployment](#pre-deployment)\n       - [Subsection 1](#subsection-1)\n       - [Subsection 2](#subsection-2)\n     - [Deployment](#deployment)\n       - [Method 1](#method-1)\n       - [Method 2](#method-2)\n   ```\n\n3. **Requirements Section**\n   - List all prerequisites with links to obtain them\n   - Include:\n     - Account requirements\n     - CLI tools needed\n     - Access permissions\n     - Software dependencies\n   - **If specific requirements unknown**: Use placeholders like:\n     - `[INSERT_CLOUD_PROVIDER] Account` (e.g., AWS Account, Azure Account)\n     - `[INSERT_CLI_TOOLS_NEEDED]` (e.g., AWS CLI, Node.js)\n     - `[INSERT_SPECIFIC_VERSIONS_IF_REQUIRED]`\n   - Example: \"Before you deploy, you must have the following:\"\n\n4. **Pre-